WorldStage Newsonline– Honeywell Flour Mills Plc, a major flour milling company in Nigeria has issued a notice to hold its 11th Annual General Meeting (AGM) on Wednesday 30th September 2020 at the Civic Centre, Ozumba Mbadiwe Street, Victoria Island Lagos at 11am. The notice at the Nigerian Stock Exchange signed by  Oluwayemisi Busari (mrs), Company Secretary said the AGM will be to receive audited financial statement for year ended 31st March 2020. It was also stated that the meeting will be to approve a dividend of 4k per share which will be paid on 30th September 2020 to shareholders whose names appear in the register as at 16th September 2020. The registers of members and transfer books of company are said to be closed from 17th September to 23rd September 2020 for the purpose of updating them.